After a few days, Jesus entered Capernaum again. And when the people heard that He was in the house, they gathered together.
A large crowd gathered, so that there was no more room. Not even outside the door was there space. And Jesus preached the word to them.
Four of those who came were carrying a man who could not walk.
But they could not bring him near Jesus because of the crowd. So they made an opening in the roof above Jesus, and when they had dug out a hole, they lowered the mat the man was lying on.
Jesus saw their faith, and he said to the man, "Child, your sins are forgiven."
And there sat in the same place scribes of the Pharisees, who thought of his matter.
