Jesus returned to the seashore of the Sea of Galilee. A large crowd gathered to him, so he got into a boat and sat down, while the whole crowd stood on the shore.
As Jesus was walking along, he saw Levi son of Alphaeus sitting at the tax collector’s booth. “Follow me,” he told him, and Levi got up and followed him.
Later, Jesus was dining at the home of Levi. There were many tax collectors and "sinners" eating with him and his disciples. They were part of the large crowd that was following Jesus.
